title: Fissility of Bi, Pb, Au, Pt, W, V, and Ti Nuclei Mesured With 100 Mev Compton Backscattering Photons.

x4freetext: FISSILITY OF BI, PB, AU, PT, W, V, AND TI NUCLEI
MESURED WITH 100 MEV COMPTON BACKSCATTERING PHOTONS.

x4codes.hlp: Inst. Yad. Fiz., Sib. A.N., Novosibirsk, Russia
INFN Laboratori Nazionali di Frascati, Frascati, Italy
Centro Brazil.de Pesquisas Fisicas, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Jour. of Physics, Part G (Nucl.and Part.Phys.), Vol.22, p.511 (1996)

x4freetext: MONOCHROMATIC PHOTON BEAM  PRODUCED  AT
THE ROKK-1M FACILITY  BY  COMPTON  BACKSCATTERING  OF
LASER  LIGHT  AGAINST  HIGH-ENERGY ELECTRONS WITH E =
1.8 GEV CIRCULATING IN THE VEPP-4M STORAGE RING.

x4codes.hlp: Inst. Yad. Fiz., Sib. A.N., Novosibirsk, Russia

x4freetext: ROKK-1M FACILITY OF BIMP, NOVOSIBIRSK.
METALIC  FOILS  OF  THE  TARGET  ELEMENTS.  ALL TARGET
MATERIALS ARE OF NATURAL ISOTOPIC COMPOSITION.
MACROFOL FISSION-TRACK-ETCH DETECTORS.
THE DIRECT FISSION FRAGMENT TRACK COUNTING.
TO OBTAIN THE FINAL VALUES OF THE PHYSICAL  QUANTITIE
AND ASSOCIATED  ERRORS,  THE  DATA  HAVE BEEN TREATED
BY CONSIDERING THE STATISTICS AND EFFICIENCY OF TRACK
COUNTING (WAS ESTIMATED TO BE ABOUT 72 - 86  %).  THE
APPROPRIATE CORRECTIONS     FOR    BOTH    GAMMA-BEAM
ATTENUATION THROUGH THE STACKS AND SELF-ABSORPTION OF
FISSION  FRAGMENTS  BY THE TARHET MATERIALS FOR THIN-
AND THICK-TARGET GEOMETRY.
THE  TOTAL - STATISTICAL   PLUS   SYSTEMATIC -
ERRORS ARE GIVEN.  SYSTEMATIC ERRORS  AMOUNT TO ABOUT
22 %  FOR BI AND AU, 18 % FOR PB, AND 13 % FOR PT, W,
TA, V, AND TI TARGETS.
DATA  WERE  PREPARED  IN THE MSU INP CDFE  BY
V.V.VARLAMOV.
PHOTOFISSION CROSS SECTIONS OF BI-209, PB-NAT, AU-197,
PT-NAT, W-NAT,  TA-181,  V-51, AND TI-NAT NUCLEI HAVE
BEEN  MEASURED  AT  THE INCIDENT PHOTON ENERGY OF 100
MEV USING MONOCHROMATIC PHOTONS PRODUCED  BY  COMPTON
BACKSCATTERING  AT  THE  ROKK-1M  FACILITY  IN  BIMP,
NOVOSIBIRSK.  DETECTION OF FISSION FRAGMENTS HAS BEEN
PERFORMED  BY  MEANS OF MACROFOL TRACK-ETCH DETECTORS
IN CLOSE CONTACT WITH METALIC  FOILS  OF  THE  TARGET
ELEMENTS.  THE VALUES OF FISSILITY AT 100 MEV DEDUCED
FOR THE TARGETS  UNDER  INVESTIGATION  ARE  FOUND  TO
RANGE BETWEEN 10**-4 AND 10**-2.  THE PRESENT RESULTS
SHOW CONSISTENCY WITH THE FISSILITY TRENDS CALCULATED
FOR  69  AND  600  MEV  MONOENERGETIC PHOTONS USING A
FORMALISM BASED ON THE  CURRENT  TWO-STEP  MODEL  FOR
INTERMEDIATE-ENERGY PHOTOFISSION REACTIONS.
